{"id":90,"date":"2004-01-25T23:44:02","date_gmt":"2004-01-26T07:44:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wordpress\/?p=90"},"modified":"2004-01-25T23:44:02","modified_gmt":"2004-01-26T07:44:02","slug":"john-perry-barlow","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2004\/01\/john-perry-barlow\/","title":{"rendered":"John Perry Barlow"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"http:\/\/barlow.typepad.com\/barlowfriendz\/\">Barlow&#8217;s new blog<\/a> is celebrated in song.  In the gutter of his blog, in his &#8220;related stuff&#8221; playlist, you can hear Haley Suitt introducing this wonderful new addition to the blogosphere.<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;John Perry Barlow is a retired Wyoming cattle rancher, a former lyricist for the <a href=\"http:\/\/dead.net\/\">Grateful Dead<\/a>, and co-founder of the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.eff.org\/\">Electronic Frontier Foundation<\/a>.&#8221; (this and more on his <a href=\"http:\/\/www.eff.org\/~barlow\/\">EFF home page<\/a>)<\/p>\n<p>I enjoyed listening to &#8220;Reimagining the Public Domain&#8221; from his &#8220;Appearances&#8221; playlist.  He talks about ideas as a lifeform, the importance of language and metaphor, and his opposition to the use of the word &#8220;content.&#8221;  Content requires a container. Thought has no container.  Since I&#8217;ve personally been involved in the creation of various software containers, I&#8217;ve often felt uneasy with the prevailing terminology.  Barlow describes the naming of content as &#8220;taking that which is immaterial, namely expression and thought, and turning it into a commercial product like a toaster.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;Information and expression is a verb and not a noun.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;The internet is not a medium it is an environment&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>&#8230; the right to know is a corollary of freedom of speech &#8230;<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;we need to preserve the right to be known, the ability of the idea to circulate.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>If you want to express yourself via MP3 in cyberspace, you can <a href=\"http:\/\/soundblox.blogspot.com\/\">set up your own SoundBlox<\/a> (free for non-commercial use).<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Barlow&#8217;s new blog is celebrated in song. In the gutter of his blog, in his &#8220;related stuff&#8221; playlist, you can hear Haley Suitt introducing this wonderful new addition to the blogosphere. &#8220;John Perry Barlow is a retired Wyoming cattle rancher, a former lyricist for the Grateful Dead, and co-founder of the Electronic Frontier Foundation.&#8221; (this&hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2004\/01\/john-perry-barlow\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2004\/01\/john-perry-barlow\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":84,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[12],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/90"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/84"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=90"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/90\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=90"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=90"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=90"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"